## Jenkins Pipeline Integration

  Component               Description
  ----------------------- --------------------------------------------
  ecosystem               Logical application name
  Environment Detection   `getEnvironments()` determines environment
  Credential Resolution   CyberArk credential mapping
  TLS Files               Certificates stored in Jenkins
  Execution               Runs `liquibase update`
  Notifications           Email on success/failure

### Sample Jenkinsfile Fragment

``` groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {
        stage('Deploy DB changes') {
            steps {
                script {
                    liquibasePipeline(
                        credentialMap: dbCredentialMap,
                        envs: getEnvironments(),
                        changelogFile: 'changelog.xml',
                        profileDir: 'Profiles/'
                    )
                }
            }
        }
    }

    post {
        success {
            mail to: emailto,
                 subject: "Liquibase SUCCESS",
                 body: "All DB changes applied."
        }
        failure {
            mail to: emailto,
                 subject: "Liquibase FAILURE",
                 body: "Check Jenkins logs."
        }
    }
}
```

